---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Workflow Automation | Intelio - Eliminate Coordination Bottlenecks" description="Eliminate coordination bottlenecks with automated workflows. Requests route themselves. Work moves continuously. No manual handoffs.">
<main class="bg-white">
  <!-- SECTION 1: HERO -->
  <section class="relative min-h-[90vh] flex items-center overflow-hidden bg-black">
    <!-- Video Background -->
    <video 
      autoplay
      muted
      loop
      playsinline
      preload="auto"
      webkit-playsinline="true"
      x5-playsinline="true"
      class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full object-cover"
      style="min-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; width: auto; height: auto;"
    >
      <source src="/videos/system-integration-hero.mp4" type="video/mp4">
      Your browser does not support the video tag.
    </video>
    
    <!-- Dark Overlay for Text Readability -->
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-black/55 z-[1]"></div>

    <div class="relative z-10 max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8 py-24 w-full">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <!-- Label -->
        <div class="mb-6">
          <span class="text-blue-400 text-sm font-bold tracking-[0.2em] uppercase">
            WORKFLOW AUTOMATION
          </span>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Headline -->
        <h1 class="text-5xl lg:text-7xl text-white leading-[1.1] mb-6 tracking-tight">
          Requests Route Themselves Automatically
        </h1>
        
        <!-- Subhead -->
        <p class="text-xl lg:text-2xl text-gray-200 mb-10 leading-relaxed">
          No manual routing. No queue delays. No bottleneck person. Work flows continuously with the right person handling each request.
        </p>
        
        <!-- CTA Button -->
        <a href="/contact" class="inline-flex items-center px-8 py-4 bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-500 text-white text-lg font-semibold rounded-xl shadow-lg hover:shadow-2xl transition-all duration-200 ease-out">
          Start a Project
          <svg class="ml-2 w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M13 7l5 5m0 0l-5 5m5-5H6" />
          </svg>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SECTION 2: INTRO -->
  <section class="py-32 px-6 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl text-gray-900 mb-8">
        Eliminate Coordination Bottlenecks. Automate Workflows.
      </h2>
      <div class="space-y-6 text-lg text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          Most businesses have one person whose job is coordination: routing requests, assigning work, managing queues. When they're unavailable, everything stops.
        </p>
        <p>
          Intelio builds workflow automations that remove the bottleneck. Requests route themselves. Work moves continuously. No manual handoffs. No queue delays.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-10 p-6 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-blue-600">
        <p class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">
          This isn't consulting. This isn't advice. It's infrastructure.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SECTION 3: WHAT'S BROKEN & WHAT CHANGES (SIDE BY SIDE) -->
  <section class="py-32 px-6 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-20 relative">
        <!-- Vertical Divider Line -->
        <div class="hidden md:block absolute left-1/2 top-0 bottom-0 w-px bg-black transform -translate-x-1/2"></div>
        
        <!-- Left Column: What's Broken Today -->
        <div class="relative">
          <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl text-gray-900 mb-12">What's Broken Today</h2>
          
          <div class="space-y-6">
            <!-- Card 1 -->
            <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 border border-gray-200 hover:border-blue-300 hover:shadow-lg transition-all duration-200 ease-out">
              <h3 class="text-2xl text-gray-900 mb-4">Manual Routing Bottleneck</h3>
              <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                Requests arrive and someone manually routes them to the right person, team, or department. This person is a bottleneck. Everything queues when they're unavailable.
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Card 2 -->
            <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 border border-gray-200 hover:border-blue-300 hover:shadow-lg transition-all duration-200 ease-out">
              <h3 class="text-2xl text-gray-900 mb-4">Work Sitting in Queues</h3>
              <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                Approval requests, lead assignments, support tickets—all waiting for someone to pick them up. Delays compound. Urgency gets lost in the queue.
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Card 3 -->
            <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 border border-gray-200 hover:border-blue-300 hover:shadow-lg transition-all duration-200 ease-out">
              <h3 class="text-2xl text-gray-900 mb-4">Inconsistent Execution</h3>
              <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                Same request gets handled differently depending on who picks it up. Lead A qualified in 2 hours, lead B in a week. Approval times are unpredictable.
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Card 4 -->
            <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 border border-gray-200 hover:border-blue-300 hover:shadow-lg transition-all duration-200 ease-out">
              <h3 class="text-2xl text-gray-900 mb-4">Lost Context at Handoffs</h3>
              <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                Work passes from person A to person B and critical context is lost. "Why is this flagged urgent?" Information is fragmented across emails and systems.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Right Column: What Changes After Deployment -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl text-gray-900 mb-12">What Changes After Deployment</h2>
          
          <div class="space-y-6">
            <!-- Card 1 -->
            <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 border border-gray-200 hover:border-blue-300 hover:shadow-lg transition-all duration-200 ease-out">
              <h3 class="text-2xl text-gray-900 mb-4">Automatic Routing & Assignment</h3>
              <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                Requests route themselves based on rules (skill, capacity, geography, complexity). No manual bottleneck. No queue delays waiting for someone to route.
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Card 2 -->
            <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 border border-gray-200 hover:border-blue-300 hover:shadow-lg transition-all duration-200 ease-out">
              <h3 class="text-2xl text-gray-900 mb-4">Work Flows Continuously</h3>
              <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                Requests are assigned and work begins within minutes, not days. Nothing sits waiting for someone to pick it up manually.
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Card 3 -->
            <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 border border-gray-200 hover:border-blue-300 hover:shadow-lg transition-all duration-200 ease-out">
              <h3 class="text-2xl text-gray-900 mb-4">Consistent Execution</h3>
              <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                Same workflow, same rules, every time. Approval times are predictable. Lead qualification is consistent. Response times are uniform across the team.
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Card 4 -->
            <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 border border-gray-200 hover:border-blue-300 hover:shadow-lg transition-all duration-200 ease-out">
              <h3 class="text-2xl text-gray-900 mb-4">Context Travels with Work</h3>
              <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                When work is assigned, all relevant information moves with it. Customer history, previous interactions, decision context. No scrambling to find context.
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Card 5 -->
            <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 border border-gray-200 hover:border-blue-300 hover:shadow-lg transition-all duration-200 ease-out">
              <h3 class="text-2xl text-gray-900 mb-4">Automatic Status Updates</h3>
              <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                Status changes trigger notifications automatically. Requestors, managers, and stakeholders stay informed without asking. Information flows instead of being manually copied.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SECTION 5: HOW IT WORKS -->
  <section class="py-32 px-6 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl text-gray-900 mb-12">How the System Actually Works</h2>
      
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <!-- Card 1 -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 border border-gray-200">
          <h3 class="text-xl text-gray-900 mb-4">Input Layer</h3>
          <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            Work enters from multiple sources: form submissions, system events (deal closed, invoice received), email, API calls, scheduled triggers. The system captures who submitted it, what it's about, when it arrived, any attachments, and where it came from.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Card 2 -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 border border-gray-200">
          <h3 class="text-xl text-gray-900 mb-4">Classification & Enrichment</h3>
          <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            The system classifies what type of work this is (support ticket, approval, lead, claim). It enriches the request with context: customer history, related records, previous similar requests, templates, and relevant business rules. This happens in seconds automatically.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Card 3 -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 border border-gray-200">
          <h3 class="text-xl text-gray-900 mb-4">Routing Decision</h3>
          <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            Rules determine who should handle this. Which team has expertise? Who has capacity? Is there geographic routing? Are there escalation rules (high-value to senior person, urgent to specialist)? The system applies your rules automatically.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Card 4 -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 border border-gray-200">
          <h3 class="text-xl text-gray-900 mb-4">Assignment & Execution</h3>
          <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            Work is assigned to the right person with full context, suggested action, SLA deadline, and links to related records. Status notifications go out automatically. If workflows can auto-execute (templated responses, task creation), they do. If they need approval, the approval request goes to the right person.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SECTION 6: ENGAGEMENT MODELS -->
  <section class="py-32 px-6 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl text-gray-900 mb-12">Engagement Models</h2>
      
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <!-- Card 1: Build + Maintain -->
        <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-xl p-8 border border-gray-200">
          <h3 class="text-xl text-gray-900 mb-2">Build + Maintain</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-6">You own the workflows. We keep the system running.</p>
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <div>
              <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-2">You Own</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Day-to-day workflow monitoring, routing rules, exception handling, SLA accountability</p>
            </div>
            <div>
